Bug reported by: jeffrey.theisen@utah.edu

Description:
For relational and logical functions I would like to use the syntax &&, ||, ==, >=, and so on (I am not sure the technical term for this syntax).  However, the functions only accept the syntax and(), or(), geq(), etc. as valid formulas.  Furthermore, after I type in formulas they sometimes get changed from geq() syntax to >= syntax, so I have to retype the entire formula if I want to change just one piece.

